column1: A 100 bedroom mansion built in 1731 for the viscounts Langford.
In 1921 the Irish Republican Army took the estate and lands, and set fire to the house which was completey destroyed.
Whilst the observer was iniitally Lord Langford, James Morse Lauder took the observation until the 1910s when W Lauder took over and continued until the end of the record in 1940.
